    public class JIconList<T>
extends javax.swing.JList<T>
    A list control that will draw icons for any added items that are IconProviders.

    3.00

    • Method Detail

      • getDefaultIcon

        public javax.swing.Icon getDefaultIcon()
        Returns the current default icon for this list. The default icon will be used by list items that either do not implement IconProvider or return null from IconProvider.getIcon().
        Returns:
        the default icon

      • setDefaultIcon

        public void setDefaultIcon​(javax.swing.Icon defaultIcon)
        Change the default icon to use for items that do not provide their own. The initial value is null, meaning that these items will not show an icon.
        Parameters:
        defaultIcon - the default icon to set

      • createRenderer

        public static <E> javax.swing.ListCellRenderer<E> createRenderer()
        Creates an JIconList.IconRenderer cast to a renderer for the specified type. The type may or may not be an IconProvider; if the actual values seen by the renderer are icon providers, their icons are used as icons for the list items.
        Type Parameters:
        E - the desired item type
        Returns:
        a list cell renderer for the specified type that renders icons for icon provider items
